\section*{Appendix A: Glossary}

\begin{multicols}{2}
\textbf{$\Phi_t(x)$} — Discrete phase at node $x$ and time $t$ \\
\textbf{$\Delta_{\text{core}}$} — Fundamental reversible lattice steps \\
\textbf{$P, PB_j$} — Pointer fields and pointer bundles \\
\textbf{$G_4$} — Harmonic basis group \\
\textbf{$L_k$} — Stabilized pointer-landmark cluster \\
\textbf{$R$} — Morphic curvature; $R=0$ is harmonic equilibrium \\
\textbf{$G_{\text{stab}}$} — Stabilizer group preserving $R=0$ \\
\textbf{$B$} — Invariant basis of harmonic manifold \\
\textbf{$Q(x)$} — Quotient coordinate map for compressed evolution \\
\textbf{$\sigma_i$} — Morphic coherence parameter \\
\textbf{VM Layer} — Isolated virtual morphic sandbox \\
\textbf{PWP} — Pointer Wave Plan (ROM evolution template) \\
\textbf{$f_{\text{edge}}$} — Edge-phase harmonic function \\
\textbf{$v\Delta R$} — Differential of morphic curvature in motion; vanishing at unity.
\end{multicols}

\section*{Appendix B: Example Local Update Rule}

For local trit-field updates:
\[
\Phi_{t+1}(x) =
\Phi_t(x) + \sum_{\Delta \in \Delta_{\text{core}}} 
    w_\Delta \bigl(\Phi_t(x+\Delta) - \Phi_t(x)\bigr) \bmod 3,
\]
where weights $w_\Delta$ are integer harmonics determined by the local pointer phase key.

\section*{Appendix C: Discrete Laplacian Definition}

The morphic Laplacian is defined as:
\[
\nabla^2_{\mathbb{Z}_3} \Phi(x) =
\sum_{\Delta \in \Delta_{\text{core}}} 
    \bigl(\Phi(x+\Delta) - 2\Phi(x) + \Phi(x-\Delta)\bigr) \bmod 3.
\]
This operator preserves reversibility and defines all wave propagation in the discrete harmonic manifold.

